    "short_descriptor": "Catchall for balanced, classic American residential design rooted in Colonial Revival.",
    "background_prose": "'Traditional' is the most-used and least-precise American home style descriptor. In practice it refers to balanced, symmetric, classically proportioned homes that draw loosely on Colonial Revival, English country house, and Georgian precedents. The style is the default 'safe' choice for production builders and older Florida suburban neighborhoods. Key features include a balanced symmetric facade, two-story proportions, red brick or muted clapboard siding, multi-pane windows with painted shutters, and a covered stoop entry with a small portico.",
